name: Comment
comment:
See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_TCP_and_UDP_port_numbers for available ports

Range 42000-42080 seems to have no ports. There are many more ranges

When creating a new app, ensure you not only define the port here, but also in
rawStatement:
export const ports = {
  //server
  "function-server": 42000,

  // page types (the components here are very specialized in functionality, the components presented here can be used as "plugin" into any app)
  "db-web": 42002,
  "markdown-reader-web": 42004,
  "function-web": 42011,
  "writer-web": 42007,

  // typerepo ()
  "search-web": 42001,
  "operation-web": 42003,
  "bundle-web": 42013,

  // demos and niches
  "passionfruit-web": 3000,
  "asset-demo-web": 42005,
  "learn-toki-web": 42006,
  "himalayajeep-web": 42008,
  "peer-web": 42012,
  "todo-web": 42014,
  "payment-web": 42015,
  "codestorys-web": 42016,
  "code-from-nepal-web": 42017,
  "code-from-brazil-web": 42018,
  "code-from-bali-web": 42019,
  "code-from-anywhere-web": 42020,
} as const;
